article.headline: Utah St. 72, St. Peter's 47
article.story: LOGAN, Utah -- Morgan Grim had 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead Utah State to a 72-47 victory against St. Peter's on Wednesday night in the Athletes in Action Holiday Classic. Brockeith Pane added 12 points and four assists for the Aggies (7-5). Marcese Tucker scored 12 points, all in the second half, for St. Peter's (2-9). Darius Conley had six points and seven rebounds. The Aggies led by 28 points in the second-half and typically had little trouble breaking the full-court pressure by the Peacocks, resulting in easy shots in the paint or trips to the free-throw line. St. Peter's shot 32 percent (18 of 56) from the field. Utah State shot 25 of 52 (48 percent) from the floor and 18 of 23 from the line.
